HEADWORD: Stayer
<hw>Stay"er</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
upholds or supports that which props; one who, or that which, stays,
stops, or restrains; also, colloquially, a horse, man, etc., that has
endurance, as in a race.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

